# Cursor plans — PLANS folder

All implementation plans created via Cursor (writing-plans, Plan mode, or similar) **must** be saved under `PLANS/` — not `docs/superpowers/plans/`, `.cursor/plans/`, or the repo root.

## Folder layout

```text
PLANS/
  integrated/       # Plans whose work is merged or otherwise complete
  not-integrated/   # Plans not yet implemented (default for new plans)
```

## Numbering

Every new plan gets the **next sequential 3-digit number** across **both** subfolders.

1. List files in `PLANS/integrated/` and `PLANS/not-integrated/`.
2. Parse leading `NNN-` from each filename (e.g. `003-auth.md` → 3).
3. Next number = max + 1, zero-padded to 3 digits (`001`, `002`, …).

## New plan path

Save new plans to:

```text
PLANS/not-integrated/NNN-<short-kebab-feature-name>.md
```

Example: `PLANS/not-integrated/002-merchant-settings.md`

## After implementation

When the plan’s work is merged (or the user confirms it is done), **move** the file to:

```text
PLANS/integrated/NNN-<short-kebab-feature-name>.md
```

Keep the same `NNN-` prefix when moving — do not renumber.

## Plan header

Include at the top of every plan:

```markdown
**Plan #:** NNN
**Status:** not integrated | integrated
**Created:** YYYY-MM-DD
```

Update `Status` and move the file when integration is complete.
